Models of Arousal

the RSMs of SCR will be tested against two models:

the Nearest Neighborhood model which assumes that the closer trials are in arousal, the more similar they are
from the Anna Karenina (AK) model which assumes that trials with high arousal will be more similar to each other than those rates as low arousal, we will derive the inverted model (Inverted AK Model), which assumes that lower values of arousal are similar to each other, but higher values are more dissimilar
